---
description: Non-negotiable engineering rules
alwaysApply: true
---
- Strict TS + strict ESLint. No `any`, no `eslint-disable`, no `@ts-ignore`, no `@ts-expect-error`, no `!` assertion.
- No TS `enum` — as-const objects + derived types. No magic strings for domain values.
- Zero inline definitions: no inline types/interfaces/constants/DTOs/schemas/config maps — dedicated folders only.
  Enforced by `architecture/no-inline-domain-definitions` (backend — now also bans module-level value/config `const` in apps/api layer files; exempt: function consts, `new`/call wiring, `LOG_CONTEXT`/`LOG_PREFIX`) and `frontend-architecture/no-inline-declarations` (web). `*.variants.ts` is the only home for design-system class strings.
- TSX = pure JSX composition. No hooks/handlers/logic in components. Pages are composition only.
- Split components into small chunks: `*.component.tsx`/`*.container.tsx` capped by `max-lines` (130) · `max-lines-per-function` (60) · `react/jsx-max-depth` — tighter than the 300/80 base. A `.component.tsx` is pure JSX (no hooks via `no-hooks-in-components`; no logic/`.map()`/inline handlers via `no-inline-component-logic`); views that map lists or hold body vars are `.container.tsx`.
- Backend layers one-way: api → application (use-case/service) → domain → infrastructure/adapters.
  Controllers delegate exactly one application call per handler.
- Frontend: Component → Hook → Service → Gateway.
- Validation is Zod only (zod pipe at the boundary); class-validator is forbidden.
- Vendor ownership: every third-party library wrapped. No direct SDK imports outside adapters.
  No raw fetch/axios outside the HTTP wrapper. No raw browser storage outside the storage wrapper.
- No `process.env` outside config/bootstrap. Logging via `AppLogger` (pino) only — never `console.*`.
- Errors are typed `AppError` with messageKey `errors.<feature>.<key>`; never leak stacks/provider errors.
- The game is FREE — no payment capture, no paid gating, ever (sole exception: the voluntary env-driven PayPal.me donate LINK; the app never processes money). No biometrics/identity matching/image storage.
- All user-facing strings via i18n. Tests first. Never weaken rules to pass.
- Gates green before done: lint (0/0) · typecheck · test:unit · test:coverage · build · security:scan.
- Conventional commits via Husky hooks; never `--no-verify`.
